# Trivy ignore list — pgvector/pgvector:pg16-trixie gosu Go stdlib CVEs
#
# All 16 CVEs are in the `gosu` binary (Go 1.24.6) bundled inside the
# pgvector image. gosu is a privilege-dropping helper used once at
# container startup (gosu postgres postgres) — it is NOT a network
# service and is not reachable by any attacker after startup.
#
# The PostgreSQL database is bound to 127.0.0.1 only (infra/docker-compose.yml,
# CI services) — the Go stdlib DoS surface is not exposed.
#
# Upstream fix exists (Go 1.25.x / 1.26.x) but pgvector maintainer has
# not rebuilt the image with a newer Go toolchain. See ADR §12.35 for
# full rationale + compensating controls.
#
# Remove these entries when pgvector publishes an image with Go >= 1.25.9.

